<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="357" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thaia) Ghauri" authorityName="Ghauri" box="[597,842,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Thaia">
<emphasis box="[597,662,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Thaia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[679,744,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Thaia</emphasis>
) Ghauri
</taxonomicName>
, but the anal tube appendage, the pygofer ventral appendage and the aedeagus are very different from the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[741,854,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[741,854,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">T. subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of the latter. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuoh" authorityYear="1982" box="[1068,1182,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parathaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1182,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="357">Parathaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has robust appendages extending from the basal lower margin of the anal tube, an unexpanded base of the pygofer ventral appendage and a large, compressed dorsal apodeme of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
